cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this dataset, please cite it as below."
type: dataset
title: "AI_Emotions_Corpus"
version: "1.0"
date-released: "2026"
doi: ""
abstract: >
  A contrastive corpus for the discourse-pragmatic analysis of artificial
  empathy and emotionally supportive language in human–AI interaction.
  The dataset combines controlled elicited dialogues with ChatGPT,
  naturally occurring user-shared Replika interactions, and public
  metapragmatic commentary from Reddit and app-store reviews.
  Total: 55 items across three subcorpora.
